From: Kuniyuki Iwashima <kuniyu@google.com>
Date: Wed, 11 Mar 2026 05:19:53 +0000
Subject: smack: Remove IPPROTO_UDPLITE support in security_sock_rcv_skb().
Patch-mainline: Queued in subsystem maintainer repository
Git-repo: https://git.kernel.org/pub/scm/linux/kernel/git/netdev/net-next.git/
Git-commit: b972cb5d397e0e9575d953a6c6b983c708de0326
References: jsc#PED-16048

smack_socket_sock_rcv_skb() is registered as socket_sock_rcv_skb,
which is called as security_sock_rcv_skb() in sk_filter_trim_cap().

Now that UDP-Lite is gone, let's remove the IPPROTO_UDPLITE support
in smack_socket_sock_rcv_skb().

Signed-off-by: Kuniyuki Iwashima <kuniyu@google.com>
Reviewed-by: Willem de Bruijn <willemb@google.com>
Acked-by: Casey Schaufler <casey@schaufler-ca.com>
Link: https://patch.msgid.link/20260311052020.1213705-7-kuniyu@google.com
Signed-off-by: Jakub Kicinski <kuba@kernel.org>
Acked-by: Fernando Fernandez Mancera <fmancera@suse.de>
---
 security/smack/smack_lsm.c |    4 +---
 1 file changed, 1 insertion(+), 3 deletions(-)

--- a/security/smack/smack_lsm.c
+++ b/security/smack/smack_lsm.c
@@ -4082,7 +4082,6 @@ static int smk_skb_to_addr_ipv6(struct s
 			sip->sin6_port = th->source;
 		break;
 	case IPPROTO_UDP:
-	case IPPROTO_UDPLITE:
 		uh = skb_header_pointer(skb, offset, sizeof(_udph), &_udph);
 		if (uh != NULL)
 			sip->sin6_port = uh->source;
@@ -4207,8 +4206,7 @@ static int smack_socket_sock_rcv_skb(str
 #if IS_ENABLED(CONFIG_IPV6)
 	case PF_INET6:
 		proto = smk_skb_to_addr_ipv6(skb, &sadd);
-		if (proto != IPPROTO_UDP && proto != IPPROTO_UDPLITE &&
-		    proto != IPPROTO_TCP)
+		if (proto != IPPROTO_UDP && proto != IPPROTO_TCP)
 			break;
 #ifdef SMACK_IPV6_SECMARK_LABELING
 		skp = smack_from_skb(skb);
